{"name": "python-cli-scheduler", "metadata": {"name": "python-cli-scheduler", "version": "1.1.2", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/hoangthanhlamm/python-cli-scheduler", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Support scheduling of task via command line interface.", "upload_time": 1735112138}, "documentation": ["# CLI Scheduler\n\nLibrary support scheduling of task via command line interface.\n\n## Installation\n```shell\npip3 install python-cli-scheduler\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nScheduler format: `^<run_now>@<interval>/<delay>$<end_timestamp>#<retry>`\n\nParameters:\n\n- `run_now`: Execute now. Default: `True`\n- `interval`: Repeat execute after number of seconds. If set to `None`, execute one time and not repeat. Default: `None`\n- `delay`: Execute at second `delay`-th at each interval. Default: `0\n- `end_time`: Execute until `end_time`. If set to `None`, infinite repeat. Default: `None`\n- `retry`: Retry if exception when executed. Default: `True`\n\n### Use with decorator\n\nComing soon\n\n### Use with scheduler job class\n\nExample job to print a lucky number at second 3 every minute.\n\n```python\nimport time\nimport random\n\nfrom cli_scheduler.scheduler_job import SchedulerJob\n\n\nclass RotationLuckJob(SchedulerJob):\n    def __init__(self, scheduler):\n        super().__init__(scheduler=scheduler)\n\n    def _pre_start(self):\n        self.logger.info('Rotation luck. Have fun !')\n        \n    def _start(self):\n        self.n = random.randint(0, 1000)\n\n    def _execute(self, *args, **kwargs):\n        self.logger.info(f'The lucky number is {self.n}')\n    \n    def _end(self):\n        del self.n\n        \n    def _follow_end(self):\n        self.logger.info('Done')\n\n        \nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    end_time = int(time.time()) + 5 * 60\n\n    # ^false: Not execute now\n    # @60: Repeat execute every 60 second\n    # /3: Execute at second 3\n    # ${end_time}: Run until end_time\n    # #false: Don't retry if exception when execute\n    job = RotationLuckJob(scheduler=f'^false@60/3${end_time}#false')\n    job.run()\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "cli_scheduler", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "cli_scheduler.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "cli_scheduler.scheduler_handle", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "cli_scheduler.scheduler_handle.scheduler_handle", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "schedule", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "cli_scheduler.constants.time_constants", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "cli_scheduler.constants.time_constants.SLEEP_DURATION", "type": null, "documentation": ["seconds"]}], "classes": [{"name": "cli_scheduler.constants.time_constants.TimeConstants", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "cli_scheduler.constants.time_constants.TimeConstants.A_HOUR", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cli_scheduler.constants.time_constants.TimeConstants.A_DAY", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cli_scheduler.constants.time_constants.TimeConstants.DAYS_30", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "cli_scheduler.constants.time_constants.TimeInterval", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "cli_scheduler.constants.time_constants.TimeInterval.hourly", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cli_scheduler.constants.time_constants.TimeInterval.daily", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cli_scheduler.constants.time_constants.TimeInterval.weekly", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cli_scheduler.constants.time_constants.TimeInterval.monthly"